Running Stereo Camera d435i on Ros2, Display Rviz2

ROS 2 humble is installed, 


1. Connect Camera to Ross
Launch RealSenese 
(source is ROS2)
	source /opt/ros/humble/setup.bash
	ros2 launch realsense2_camera rs_launch.py pointcloud.enable:=true

Output: Node is up (means the system is running) 

2. Open RViz2
(source is ROS2)
	source /opt/ros/humble/setup.bash
	rviz2

TO run Camera and PointCloud
  -Fixed Frame: camera_link

  Add
   By topic
      - /camera  
        -/camera 
            -image_raw
              camera
      - /depth
        - /color
          - /points
              PointCloud2

Install the package from this https://github.com/Slamtec/sllidar_ros2. 
Run RpLidar A2M1

	ros2 launch rplidar_ros view_rplidar_a2m12_launch.py
	**This command is use to open rviz automatically

Run Lidar without opening Rviz2
	source /opt/ros/humble/setup.bash
	source ~/ros2_ws/install/setup.bash
	ros2 launch rplidar_ros rplidar_a2m12_launch.py

Steps to Run Lidar and Camera
       New Terminal 1
			1. Run Lidar without opening Rviz2
       
       New Terminal 2
			2. Connect Camera to Ross
       
       New Terminal 3
        	Enter Command:
        	3. ros2 run tf2_ros static_transform_publisher 0 0 0 0 0 0 camera_link laser
	
       Newe Terminal 4
    		4. Open RViz2



    
